I think it's great. An over the top morbid joke is even funnier being so out of place in a cute slice of life comic.

You can't waste a page of the comic on the kid being cured and going home. You can keep exploring humorous attempts at cures, which builds up anticipation for the payoff, but the longer you do it the less satisfying any conclusion is. Or you can cure him and do the tired punchline of turning him right back into stone again (or maybe his sister and now the roles are reversed) and call that an ending.

Rockboy floating in the infinite cosmic void is funny, original enough, AND it doesn't take any of the easy ways out. 9/10 writing.
